# QuartoReview — Desktop Configuration
#
# This file is your personal configuration for QuartoReview.
# Edit it with any text editor (Notepad works fine).
#
# IMPORTANT: Lines starting with # are comments and are ignored by the app.
#            The two lines you MUST fill in (SESSION_SECRET and GITHUB_TOKEN)
#            do NOT start with # — make sure they stay that way.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# SESSION_SECRET
# ──────────────
# A random private string used to secure your login session.
# You do not need to remember this — just paste any long random text.
# A good option: open https://www.uuidgenerator.net/ and paste the result.
# Replace the placeholder below with your own value.
SESSION_SECRET=replace-this-with-any-long-random-string

# GITHUB_TOKEN
# ────────────
# Your GitHub Personal Access Token (PAT). This lets QuartoReview read
# and save files in your GitHub repositories.
#
# How to create one:
#   1. Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens/new?scopes=repo
#      (log in if asked)
#   2. Give it a name like "QuartoReview"
#   3. Make sure the "repo" checkbox is ticked
#   4. Click "Generate token" at the bottom
#   5. Copy the token — it starts with ghp_
#      (you can only see it once, so copy it immediately)
#   6. Paste it below, replacing the placeholder
#
# The token looks like: ghp_A1b2C3d4E5f6G7h8I9j0K1l2M3n4O5p6
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_replace_this_with_your_actual_token
